-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Determine the sum of the distinct prime divisors of the sum of all positive divisors of 500. 2. [Key Idea] Use the multiplicative divisor–sum formula σ(n)=∏(p_i^{a_i+1}−1)/(p_i−1) to compute A=σ(500) exactly, then factor A and add its distinct primes. 3. [Proof] a) Factor 500: 500 = 2² · 5³. b) Apply the divisor–sum formula: σ(500) = σ(2²) · σ(5³) = (2³−1)/(2−1) · (5⁴−1)/(5−1) = (8−1)/1 · (625−1)/4 = 7 · 156 = 1092. c) Factor 1092: 1092 = 2 · 546 = 2² · 273 = 2² · 3 · 91 = 2² · 3 · 7 · 13. d) Distinct prime divisors of 1092: 2, 3, 7, 13. Their sum: 2 + 3 + 7 + 13 = 25. 4. [Conclusion] The sum of the distinct prime divisors of σ(500) is 25.
